they
would
give
us
fewer
pictures
chequered
with
vivid
contrasts
of
light
and
shade;
they
would
seldom
elevate
their
heroes
and
heroines
to
the
heights
of
rapture
still
seldomer
sink
them
to
the
depths
of
despair;
for
if
we
rarely
taste
the
fulness
of
joy
in
this
life,
we
yet
more
rarely
savour
the
acrid
