I
never
had
a
smile
for
his
raillery,
never
a
moment
for
his
society;
his
invitations
to
take
coffee
with
him
in
his
parlour
were
invariably
rejected,
and
very
stiffly
and
sternly
rejected
too;
his
jesting
allusions
to
the
directress
(which
he
still
continued)
were
heard
with
a
grim
