of
his
brow,
a
constant
examination
and
comparison
of
premises,
and
an
anxious
endeavour
to
draw
thence
some
explanatory
inference.
Ere
long,
I
fancy,
he
succeeded,
for
he
was
not
without
penetration;
perhaps,
too,
Mdlle.
Zoraide
might
have
aided
him
in
the
solution
of
the
enigma;
at
any
rate
I
soon
found
that
the
uncertainty
of
doubt
had
vanished
from
