And
then,
as
I
walked
fast
along
the
road,
there
rose
upon
me
a
strange,
inly
felt
idea
of
some
Great
Being,
unseen,
but
all
present,
who
in
His
beneficence
desired
only
my
welfare,
and
now
watched
the
struggle
of
good
and
evil
in
my
heart,
and
waited
to
see
whether
I
should
obey
His
voice,
heard
in
the
whispers
of
my
conscience,
or
lend
an
ear
to
the
sophisms
by
which
His
enemy
and
mine
the
Spirit
of
Evil
sought
to
lead
