and
address
myself
to
the
rude
ascent;
so,
on
the
other
hand,
each
inclination
to
the
velvet
declivity
seemed
to
kindle
a
gleam
of
triumph
on
the
brow
of
the
man
hating,
God
defying
demon.
Sharp
and
short
I
turned
round;
fast
I
retraced
my
steps;
in
half
an
hour
I
was
again
at
M.
Pelet's:
I
sought
him
in
his
study;
brief
