I
had
received
such
marks
of
attention
occasionally,
and
with
me,
who
had
no
friends,
correspondence
of
more
interest
was
out
of
the
question;
the
postman's
arrival
had
never
yet
been
an
event
of
interest
to
me
since
I
came
to
Brussels.
I
laid
my
hand
carelessly
on
the
documents,
and
coldly
and
slowly
glancing
at
them,
I
prepared
to
break
the
seals;
my
