as
a
learned
grisette.
One
afternoon,
Mrs.
Wharton
brought
in
a
Parisian
lady
to
test
the
accuracy
of
my
knowledge
of
French;
the
result
of
it
was
that,
owing
probably
in
a
great
degree
to
the
mother's
and
daughter's
good
humour
about
the
marriage,
which
inclined
them
to
do
beneficent
