met
and
satisfied
the
wish
of
my
heart.
Two
results
of
her
letter
were
then
pleasant,
sweet
as
two
draughts
of
nectar;
but
applying
my
lips
for
the
third
time
to
the
cup,
and
they
were
excoriated
as
with
vinegar
and
gall.
Two
persons
whose
desires
are
moderate
may
live
well
enough
in
Brussels
on
an
income
which
would
scarcely
afford
a
respectable
maintenance
for
one
in
London:
and
that,
not
because
the
necessaries
of
life
are
so
much
