of
a
hundred
genteel
English
mansions.
In
Belgium,
provided
you
can
make
money,
you
may
save
it;
this
is
scarcely
possible
in
England;
ostentation
there
lavishes
in
a
month
what
industry
has
earned
in
a
year.
More
shame
to
all
classes
in
that
most
bountiful
and
beggarly
country
for
their
servile
following
of
Fashion;
I
could
write
a
chapter
or
two
on
this
subject,
but
must
forbear,
at
least
for
the
present.
Had
I
retained
my
60l.
per
annum
I
could,
now
that
Frances
was
in
possession
of
50l.,
have
gone
straight
to
her
this
very
