an
hour
from
the
wall
to
the
window;
and
at
the
window,
self
reproach
seemed
to
face
me;
at
the
wall,
self
disdain:
all
at
once
out
spoke
Conscience:
"Down,
stupid
tormenters!"
cried
she;
"the
man
has
done
his
duty;
you
shall
not
bait
him
thus
by
