in
the
outskirts
of
Brussels,
of
which
I
do
not
at
this
moment
remember
the
name,
but
near
it
were
several
of
those
lakelets
called
etangs;
and
there
was
one
etang,
larger
than
the
rest,
where
on
holidays
people
were
accustomed
to
amuse
themselves
by
rowing
round
it
in
