It
appeared,
then,
that
I
too
was
a
sensualist,
in
my
temperate
and
fastidious
way.
Now,
reader,
during
the
last
two
pages
I
have
been
giving
you
honey
fresh
from
flowers,
but
you
must
not
live
entirely
on
food
so
