an
ouvriere!
And
I
pitied
the
fellow,
thinking
his
feelings
had
misled
him,
and
that
he
had
hurt
himself
by
contracting
a
low
match!"
"Just
let
go
my
collar,
Hunsden."
On
the
contrary,
he
swayed
me
to
and
fro;
so
I
grappled
him
round
