on
the
turf
of
this
lane
generally
appear
the
first
daisies
of
spring
whence
its
name
Daisy
Lane;
serving
also
as
a
distinction
to
the
house.
It
terminates
(the
lane
I
mean)
in
a
valley
full
of
wood;
which
wood
chiefly
oak
and
beech
spreads
shadowy
about
the
vicinage
of
a
very
old
mansion,
one
of
the
Elizabethan
structures,
much
larger,
as
well
as
more
antique
than
Daisy
Lane,
the
property
and
residence
of
an
individual
familiar
