heart,
repeated
"He
might
have
been
cured
you
should
have
tried
you
should
have
burnt
the
wound
with
a
hot
iron,
or
covered
it
with
caustic.
You
gave
no
time;
and
now
it
is
too
late
he
is
dead!"
He
sank
fairly
down
on
the
senseless
carcase;
I
waited
patiently
a
long
while,
till
his
grief
had
somewhat
exhausted
him;
and
then
I
lifted
him
in
my
arms
and
carried
him
to
his
mother,
sure
that
she
would
comfort
him
best.
She
had
witnessed
the
whole
scene
from
a
window;
she
would
not
come
out
for
fear
of
increasing
my
difficulties
by
her
