Victor
has
a
preference
for
Hunsden,
full
as
strong
as
I
deem
desirable,
being
considerably
more
potent,
decided,
and
indiscriminating,
than
any
I
ever
entertained
for
that
personage
myself.
Frances,
too,
regards
it
with
a
sort
of
unexpressed
anxiety;
while
her
son
leans
on
